pageContext.claim: “Minnesota has added more than 7,500 brand new mining, logging, and construction jobs, which nobody expected.”
pageContext.analysis: Mining, logging and construction jobs have fluctuated in Minnesota since Trump took office. There are roughly 11,000 more jobs in this sector in March 2019 than there were in February 2017, but that is 25,000 lower than its peak in August 2018.
